                            <comment id="12573780" author="arnaudsimon" created="Fri, 29 Feb 2008 15:13:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The folowing tests don&apos;t do a proper resource cleaning: &lt;br/&gt;
client/src/test/java/org/apache/qpid/test/unit/basic/close/CloseTests.java&lt;br/&gt;
client/src/test/java/org/apache/qpid/test/unit/basic/InvalidDestinationTest.java&lt;br/&gt;
client/src/test/java/org/apache/qpid/test/unit/basic/LargeMessageTest.java&lt;br/&gt;
client/src/test/java/org/apache/qpid/test/unit/basic/PubSubTwoConnectionTest.java&lt;br/&gt;
client/src/test/java/org/apache/qpid/test/unit/client/AMQConnectionTest.java&lt;br/&gt;
client/src/test/java/org/apache/qpid/test/unit/client/connection/ConnectionTest.java&lt;br/&gt;
client/src/test/java/org/apache/qpid/test/unit/client/message/ObjectMessageTest.java&lt;br/&gt;
client/src/test/java/org/apache/qpid/test/unit/close/CloseBeforeAckTest.java&lt;br/&gt;
client/src/test/java/org/apache/qpid/test/unit/message/StreamMessageTest.java&lt;br/&gt;
client/src/test/java/org/apache/qpid/test/unit/topic/TopicPublisherTest.java&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would be good if somebody can double check whether this list is exhaustive. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12575715" author="arnaudsimon" created="Thu, 6 Mar 2008 14:20:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have checked in a patch for the above tests to close resources. I have also changed DurableSubscriptionTest#testDurability to unsubscribe the durable subscriber as the session is created as no ack the test cannot be run twice in a row because messages are redelivered (messages are not acked) &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12575774" author="rhs" created="Thu, 6 Mar 2008 17:01:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Rather than closing connections manually in each test case, we could probably modify QpidTestCase to track the connections that it gives out via it&apos;s getConnection(..) methods, and automatically close them on teardown. This would at least narrow the problem to only those tests that don&apos;t extend QpidTestCase, which should be a diminishing number.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12653806" author="arnaudsimon" created="Fri, 5 Dec 2008 14:50:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is solved but as mentioned QpidTestcase will benefit in closing the connection. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
